xplain away the clear evidence that human activity has changed Earth's climate. Toles's cartoons collapse counter-scientific strategies into their biased components, helping readers see how to best strike at these fallacies. Mann's expert skills at science communication aim to restore sanity to a debate that continues to rage against widely acknowledged scientific consensus. The synergy of these two climate science crusaders enlivens the gloom and doom of so many climate-themed books—and may even convert die-hard doubters to the side of sound science.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aClimatic changesxPsychological aspects. 0aClimatic changes. 0aDenial (Psychology) 0aDenial (Psychology). 0aGlobal warmingxPsychological aspects. 0aGlobal warming. 7aSCIENCE / Global Warming & Climate Change.2bisacsh1 aToles, Tom, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311063857840uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/mann1778640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231541817423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231541817.jpg  a978-3-11-063857-8  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK